
[1]conveniently

   CONVENIENTLY, adv.

   1. Fitly; suitably; with adaptation to the end or effect. That house is
   not conveniently situated for a tradesman.

   2. Commodiously; with ease; without trouble or difficulty. He cannot
   conveniently accept the invitation.
